renton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":1,"bookName":"Genesis","bookAbbrev":"genesis","chapter":11,"verse":25,"text":"And Nachor lived after he had begotten Tharrha, an hundred and twenty-five years, and begot sons and daughters, and he died.","searchKeywords":["and","nachor","lived","after","had","begotten","tharrha","hundred","twenty","five","years","begot","sons","daughters","died"]},{"verseId":"brenton_genesis_11_26","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":1,"bookName":"Genesis","bookAbbrev":"genesis","chapter":11,"verse":26,"text":"And Tharrha lived seventy years, and begot Abram, and Nachor, and Arrhan.","searchKeywords":["and","tharrha","lived","seventy","years","begot","abram","nachor","arrhan"]},{"verseId":"brenton_genesis_11_27","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":1,"bookName":"Genesis","bookAbbrev":"genesis","chapter":11,"verse":27,"text":"And these the generations of Tharrha. Tharrha begot Abram and Nachor, and Arrhan; and Arrhan begot Lot.","searchKeywords":["and","these","the","generations","tharrha","begot","abram","nachor","arrhan","lot"]},{"verseId":"brenton_genesis_11_28","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":1,"bookName":"Genesis","bookAbbrev":"genesis","chapter":11,"verse":28,"text":"And Arrhan died in the presence of Tharrha his father, in the land in which he was born, in the country of the Chaldees.","searchKeywords":["and","arrhan","died","the","presence","tharrha","his","father","land","which","was","born","country","chaldees"]},{"verseId":"brenton_genesis_11_29","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":1,"bookName":"Genesis","bookAbbrev":"genesis","chapter":11,"verse":29,"text":"And Abram and Nachor took to themselves wives, the name of the wife of Abram was Sara, and the name of the wife of Nachor, Malcha, daughter of Arrhan, and he was the father of Malcha, the father of Jescha.","searchKeywords":["and","abram","nachor","took","themselves","wives","the","name","wife","was","sara","malcha","daughter","arrhan","father","jescha"]},{"verseId":"brenton_genesis_11_30","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":1,"bookName":"Genesis","bookAbbrev":"genesis","chapter":11,"verse":30,"text":"And Sara was barren, and did not bear children.","searchKeywords":["and","sara","was","barren","did","not","bear","children"]},{"verseId":"brenton_genesis_11_31","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":1,"bookName":"Genesis","bookAbbrev":"genesis","chapter":11,"verse":31,"text":"And Tharrha took Abram his son, and Lot the son of Arrhan, the son of his son, and Sara his daughter-in-law, the wife of Abram his son, and led them forth out of the land of the Chaldees, to go into the land of Chanaan, and they came as far as Charrhan, and he dwelt there.","searchKeywords":["and","tharrha","took","abram","his","son","lot","the","arrhan","sara","daughter","law","wife","led","them","forth","out","land","chaldees","into","chanaan","they","came","far","charrhan","dwelt","there"]},{"verseId":"brenton_genesis_11_32","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":1,"bookName":"Genesis","bookAbbrev":"genesis","chapter":11,"verse":32,"text":"And all the days of Tharrha in the land of Charrhan were two hundred and five years, and Tharrha died in Charrhan.","searchKeywords":["and","all","the","days","tharrha","land","charrhan","were","two","hundred","five","years","died"]}]